,Recommended,252550,10235245,"Posted: 25 May, 2014",all,Green Finn,"Qbeh-1 is a good platformer. It's not bad, it's not terrible and it's certainly not amazing or astounding. It's just plain good and if you ask me - which you should since you're reading this - is something rather rare these days.People always want to make the next best blockbuster that blows everyone's minds and generates billions of dollars and whatnot. Which, granted, is fine, I get that...but Qbeh feels a lot more humble and I like that. The atmosphere is created through level and audio design combined with a good colour palette, resulting in a solid foundation for a game.It's serene and calm in the strange world of Qbeh. The slow and relaxed melodies combined with desolate but beautiful visuals gives a nice, pacifying feeling to the player. Playing this game relieves stress, well, personally speaking anyway, and I find that to a really nice and rare quality.I highly recommend it. Not because of any action - there is none to be found. Not because of any electric guitar shredding - you're in the wrong neighborhood for that. Qbeh is a game of peace, exploration and a little brain work. When you're bored of blowing everybody up with explosives, riddling them with a hail of bullets or slashing zombies to bits, play this. It helps."
