,Not Recommended,252550,10629290,"Posted: 21 June, 2014",all,Anna,"Updated Review: September 2015.After more than a year I still cannot reccommend the game.The major complaints I had last june still persist.I have a brand new, high end computer, and the gameplay still doesn't seem to get fluid.The camera seems to be slow to react, and specially when moving the camera quickly it just doesn't feel right. If you're used to playing on lower (~30) framerates you probably don't notice it, but for me it was very noticable.Another major issue is the jumping, you seem to be falling down really fast after reaching the highest point in your jump, because the game features quite a few of fairly harsh jumps this can be really annoying.The fact that I can't save when I want can be a valid design choice, but not being able to re-save again after a checkpoint can be really frustrating. If you fail a section multiple times and need to keep grabbing the same cubes it just gets frustrating. I don't understand why we can't save again after say a cooldown period of ~5 seconds.==============Original Review: June 2014Do I recommend this game?At the moment no, but if the developers fix some things I think I will:1) perfomance issues.without vsync I had some horrible screentear.with vsync I had some horrible fps2) Save pointsSome of the save points are often a pain. They can be really unforgiving and walking past them again doesn't save again. This can lead to doing things over and over again.3) Lack of personal savesI think this is a design choice but I'd liked to have a quicksave option before trying some crazy moves. Combine this with the sometimes terrible save points and it can be really frustrating to play sometimes.Some personal problems I had:- the music got on my nerves quite a bit- slow pacing, specially the first 2 worlds are very easy.The game has some good things too though:- the mechanics from the third and fourth cubes cube are really fun.- the visual style is really cool and works pretty well.- the gameplay itself is  done well, the mechanics work well.- it feels like minecraft combined with portal!"
