,Recommended,252550,14275697,"Posted: 1 February, 2015",all,ElyCyan,"Qbeh is a puzzle platformer that does not disappoint. You pick up colored cubes to place in marked positions in the map. You'll build small bridges and stairs out of these cubes to get to the next area, and, when you discover the other types of cubes, you'll be making low grav jumpways and riding cubes over precarious pits.The experience is just like the music in the game -- relaxing and beautiful. If you're looking for a thrillride or a sarcastic, witty narrator, this isn't your game.If you'd like to relax, figure out some puzzles at your own pace, this is a great game. If you're like me, you'll be hoarding cubes in an effort to break out of the map and discover secrets. This game does not disappoint in this respect either.I really enjoyed every second of this game and didn't want it to end. I can't recommend this game enough."
