76561198277332300,Recommended,252550,26300362,"Posted: 29 October, 2016",all,Clyde the Hobo,"tl;dr Buy this game on Steam then go onto iTunes and buy the soundtrack or I'll appear in your bedroom tonight and whisper hurtful nothings into your ear while you sleep.""Qbeh-1"" is a stupid name. That being said, it's about the only bad thing I can say about this game. The graphics are phenomenal, the music is all sort of atmospheric and the gameplay is about as solid as the blocks you use. I did have a few graphical glitches and a few times, my blocks vanished into the void that moment I placed them but overall this rarely happened. Full of secrets and brain-tickling puzzles, it's the kind of game that would make a certain skeleton smile."
