76561198026967461,Recommended,252550,34531408,Posted: 27 August,all,bitnykk,"Here's a proof simplicity & care can lead to a good game. The effort put on minimalistic music/ambiance, nice shadow & lighting work, the 2 level of difficulty design (ending a level being first, finding an optionnal token at same being second), the various 6x6 maps proposed, that makes already a decent overall. But if you add to that a map creation mode and its about 200 community freely subscribable maps (through Workshop section of its Steam Hub), Qbeh-1 is clearly over the average of its genre. Indeed, it would need to be slightly less sober to become a major title, but nobody would deny it's an enjoyable world to spend time in."
